Exercise 2: E-commerce Platform Search Function
1. Understanding Asymptotic Notation
Big O Notation: Big O measures how an algorithm's performance changes as the amount of data increases.
Best Case: Item is found immediately.
Average Case: Item is found after checking some elements.
Worst Case: Item is found at the end or not found at all.
2. Setup

Create  Product class with:

productId
productName
category
3. Implementation
Linear Search: Searches each product one by one in an array.
Binary Search: Searches a sorted array by repeatedly checking the middle element.
4. Analysis
Algorithm	Best	Average	Worst
Linear Search	O(1)	O(n)	O(n)
Binary Search	O(1)	O(log n)	O(log n)

Conclusion: Binary search is better for large e-commerce platforms because it is much faster than linear search,
provided the products are stored in sorted order.